name: 134747: Labuan Bajaj
description: Labuan Bajo means "Place Where the Sea Gypsies Stop Over". Labuan Bajo usually serves as the arrival point for tourists to continue on their journey to the famous Komodo National Park. With rising large number of visitors, the region faces less-than-desirable challenges, such as mounting trash, illegal fishing and coral vulnerability. And how about Labuan Bajaj?
